rom Middle English <i>burre</i> ‘bur’ (a seed-case or flower-head with clinging prickles), used by Shakespeare to denote someone who sticks like a bur, a person difficult to ‘shake off’, a sense which may well be older.","German: topographic name from <i>Burr(e)</i> ‘mound, hill’, or in the south a variant of   Burrer  .","History: The American political leader Aaron Burr (1756–1836) was the son of a clergyman and academic, president of Princeton University. On his mother's side he was descended from the Puritan preacher Jonathan Edwards; on his father's from Jehu Burr, who emigrated from England to MA with John Winthrop (see   Winthrop  ) in 1630."],"variants":[{"name":"Burrer","meanings":["German:","from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>burren</i> ‘to buzz, complain’, probably applied as a nickname for a noisy or cantankerous person.","habitational name for someone from either of two places called Burren in Württemberg."]},{"name":"Burrs","meanings":["Altered form of English   Burr  , with the addition of excrescent <i>-s</i>, or perhaps of   Burrows  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Brenchley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Kent): habitational name from a place in Kent named Brenchley, from an Old English personal name <i>Brænci</i> (of uncertain origin) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":55,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John of Brenchley Burr was born about 1400, in Brenchley, Kent, England, his father, William Brenchley, was 51 and his mother, Joan Battisford, was 35. He married Lady Elizabeth De Ros Roos in 1413, in Radwinter, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1461, in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1400–Aft 1461":"umbes 1400–pärast 1461","1375–1446":"1375–1446","1385–1453":"1385–1453","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1404–1452":"1404–1452","1420–1509":"1420–1509","1423–Male":"1423–Surnud","1350–1406":"1350–1406","1366–1453":"1366–1453","26 May 1406":"26. mai 1406","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1404":"1404","6 August 1453":"6. august 1453","1413":"1413","1446":"1446","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1366":"1366","1420":"1420","1453":"1453","1452":"1452","1375":"1375","1509":"1509","Aft 1461":"pärast 1461","1406":"1406","Radwinter, Essex, England":"Radwinter, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tudeley-cum-Capel, Tonbridge, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tudeley, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Brenchley, Kent, England":"Brenchley, Kent, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1400–Aft 1461":"noin 1400–1461 jälkeen","1375–1446":"1375–1446","1385–1453":"1385–1453","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1404–1452":"1404–1452","1420–1509":"1420–1509","1423–Male":"1423–Kuollut","1350–1406":"1350–1406","1366–1453":"1366–1453","26 May 1406":"26. toukokuuta 1406","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","1404":"1404","6 Augus